The dropdown with trigger ".issue-actions-trigger" is very handy to create dynamic dropdowns for issues and with the ActionsAndOperations REST service to create quick dropdowns. It also removes the problem of changes in markup between JIRA releases.

We would like to use this functionality outside the context of an issue. We have already done so for worklogs with great success. However, the formatSuccess function used requires an issue object (JIRA.FRAGMENTS.issueActionsFragment).

We would like to propose a new dropdown that is more generic. That is, it would be excactly like JIRA.FRAGMENTS.issueActionsFragment but without the first item (View Issue).

You could create it with something like the following:

{code}
    AJS.Dropdown.create({
        trigger: ".generic-actions-trigger",
        ajaxOptions: {
            dataType: "json",
            cache: false,
            formatSuccess: JIRA.FRAGMENTS.genericActionsFragment
        }
    });
{code}

We are aware that would could easily create this on the plugin site but that would be a major headache when supporting multiple JIRA releases. Since the genericActionsFragment would be on the JIRA end, we wouldn't have to worry about changes in the markup.

There are multiple use cases for this in our plugin development and it would save us a lot of time dealing with new JIRA releases.

It would also be convenient if the fragment would render the 'desc' attribute in the actions/operations elements as the link title.

This is something we would really want to see in JIRA 5.0 so we can throw away our old dropdowns.

