As documented in JRA-2557 and JRA-15823, when changing an issue's type (either by moving between projects or editing it within the current project) information living in custom fields which are valid on the source issue type which are not valid fields on the destination issue type will be removed when the issue type is changed.  The information lost in the field will be stored in the issue history.  If the issue type is then changed again, either back to the prior issue type or to a new issue type that shares the same custom fields as the issue's original type, the information is still lost from the fields and must be manually reentered by the user.  It would be far more useful if the field data was retrieved from the issue history and restored to the field it came from when a previously valid field for an issue again becomes available on the issue.

